{{Infobox writer <!--For more information, see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]].--> | name = Loula Anagnostaki | honorific_prefix = | honorific_suffix = | native_name = Λούλα Αναγνωστάκη | native_name_lang = el | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | pseudonym = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1928|12|13|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Thessaloniki]], [[Greece]] |death_date= {{Death date and age|2017|10|8|1928|12|13|df=y}} | death_place = | resting_place = | occupation = | language = | nationality = | citizenship = | education = | alma_mater = [[Aristotle University of Thessaloniki]] | period = | genre = <!-- or: | genres = --> | subject = <!-- or: | subjects = --> | movement = | notableworks = <!-- or: | notablework = --> | spouse = <!-- or: | spouses = --> | partner = <!-- or: | partners = --> | children = | relatives = [[Manolis Anagnostakis]] <small>(brother)</small> | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | years_active = | module = | website = | portaldisp = <!-- "on", "yes", "true", etc; or omit --> | ethnicity = }} '''Loula Anagnostaki''' (13 December 1928 – 8 October 2017) was a [[Greece|Greek]] writer. Her surname also appears as '''Anagnostakē'''.<ref name="wilson" />
==Early life and education== She was born in [[Thessaloniki]]. She was the sister of poet [[Manolis Anagnostakis]].<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=Q-lr20SuvfIC&pg=PA16 |title=Encyclopedia of Modern Greek Literature |page=16 |last=Merry |first=Bruce |year=2004 |ISBN=0313308136}}</ref> She earned a law degree from [[Aristotle University of Thessaloniki]].<ref name=miller>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=NOyZs4PRKxEC&pg=PA14 |title=Who's who in Contemporary Women's Writing |pages=14-15 |last=Miller |first=Jane Eldridge |year=2002 |ISBN=0415159814}}</ref>
==Career== Her first three one act plays were performed in 1965 and published in 1974: ''Dianyktereusē'' (Overnight stop), ''Polé'' (The City) and ''Parelasé'' (Parade).<ref name=wilson/> Her works have been performed by the [[National Theatre of Greece]] and by [[Karolos Koun]]'s Art Theatre, as well as in Cyprus, France, England, Italy and Poland.<ref name=wilson>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=2Wf1SVbGFg8C&pg=PA32 |title=An Encyclopedia of Continental Women Writers |pages=32-33 |last=Wilson |first=Katharina M |volume=Volume 1 |year=1991 |ISBN=0824085477}}</ref>
=== Selected works<ref name=miller/> === * ''E Synanastrophē'' (Social encounter), play (1967) * ''Antonio ē to menyma'' (Antonio or the message), play (1972) * ''Nikē'' (Victory), play (1978)
* '' E Kaseta'' (The tape), play (1983), published by «Κέδρος», Αθήνα 2008, {{ISBN|978-960-04-3859-8}} * ''O Ihos Tou Oplou'' (The sound of the gun), play (1986), published by «Κέδρος», Αθήνα 2007, {{ISBN|978-960-04-3653-2}} * ''Διαμάντια και μπλουζ. Το ταξίδι μακριά.''(Diamonds and Blues. The long journey.) plays published by «Κέδρος», Αθήνα 2008, {{ISBN|978-960-04-3697-6}}
